    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Presenting a museum-quality 996.2 Carrera, featuring the 3.6L naturally aspirated flat-six engine. This specimen boasts a documented IMS bearing retrofit and rear main seal replacement, mitigating common M96 failure points. Power is delivered via a 6-speed Getrag manual transaxle with a factory short-shift kit. The chassis is dialed in with the M030 Sport Chassis package, providing increased roll stiffness and optimized damping. Braking is handled by four-piston Monobloc calipers over cross-drilled rotors, showing no signs of thermal stress. The exterior retains its factory depth and luster, while the undercarriage is remarkably clean, reflecting a climate-controlled life. This is a zero-fault, investment-grade driver for the purist who demands mechanical perfection.",
